hopobject.body: I work for a publishers allopurinol 300 mg tablet Building on Washington's close ties to its GCC allies, the U.S. sought to break the deadlock of the peace process by convening Israel and the Sunni monarchies through the 1991 multilateral Madrid Conference. The U.S. diplomatic initiative contributed to the official beginning of an understanding between Israel and the GCC that shared strategic interests could accelerate the peace process. Indeed, responding to the Islamic Revolution of 1979, the pro-Western Arab monarchies formed the GCC in 1981 as a collective security pact meant to serve as a counterweight against Iran and its regional interference.
